{title: Country Pride}
{artist: Mel Street}
{composer: Written by Betty Carol}

[C]Well go ahead and call me a country boy
I couldn't hide it even if I tried
I'm a [F]country boy from the hills of old [C]Virginia
Where the [D7]country folks got lots of country [G7]pride
Well [C]daddy raised us working in a coal mine
But mama's love was always by his side
When [F]things got rough we've just got rough [C]with 'em
